1.sudo apt-get install git //installation



configuration:

1.git config --global user.name "Your Name"

2.git config --global user.email "youremail@domain.com"





We can see all of the configuration items that have been set by typing:

    git config --list

we can also edit the configuration file by hand with text editor like this:

    nano ~/.gitconfig




The next step is to create a repository in github.Then follow the following steps:

1. create a file which we need to push to github repository.
	e.g. nano test.txt

2. git add <file_name.format>

3. git commit -m "......" // command  to commit

4. git remote add origin https://github.com/ShubhaM220/repository_name.git // to make the repository available for push.

5. git push -u origin master // push to master branch






follow the following code to change the branch


-->git checkout -b my_new_branch.

then

-->git push -u origin my_new_branch.



To view log following command can be used.

-->git log




Now to clone a repository to your machine follow the below listed command:

--> git clone [urlof the repository]

important links:

1. basic command for beginers:
	http://www.dataschool.io/git-quick-reference-for-beginners/
	
	
